==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Leek
<hw>Leek</hw> <pr>(l⟦emac⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>le⟦aacute⟧c</ets>; akin to D. <ets>look</ets>, G. <ets>lauch</ets>,
OHG. <ets>louh</ets>, Icel. <ets>laukr</ets>, Sw. <ets>l⟦oum⟧k</ets>,
Dan <ets>l⟦oum⟧g</ets>. Cf. <er>Garlic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A plant of the genus <gen>Allium</gen> (<spn>Allium Porrum</spn>),
having broadly linear succulent leaves rising from a loose oblong
cylindrical bulb. The flavor is stronger than that of the common
onion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Wild leek</b></col> , <cd>in America, a plant
(<spn>Allium tricoccum</spn>) with a cluster of ovoid bulbs and large
oblong elliptical leaves.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Leeme</ent>⟦br⟧
